author: Ulquiorra Cifer
comment: I don‚Äôt like this anime for various reasons. It‚Äôs not bad, it actually started to rope me in midway, but it has some serious theme flaws. One of the themes is hard work, and Sora is the epitome of that idea. Early on, they give Sora a stupid weakness, not being able to shoot on the left side, a weakness that could easily be resolved through hard work. This anime tells me how important effort is, yet at the same time says it isn‚Äôt. Momoharu, he was bad a shooting and even layups, but after years of practice, he still couldn‚Äôt produce any results. Mokichi is another example, he played Basketball to build stamina, yet it didn‚Äôt work, yes Mokichi has a pre-existing condition, but the show is framing it as a matter of hard work. Above all else, the character designs are either ugly or repetitive in my opinion.

author: Jenny Maier
comment: So this is completely my opinion on both of those animes (knb, Uhm the Anime from the amv, sry don't know the name^^`), I apologize right way for my bad English.   I watched all of knb, included the movie and I am reading the Manga at the moment. I love that Anime, also cause I don't mind that some things are unrealistic. Some of the boys tactics are proved that they're  possible, played from NBA players. (ankle breaker, some of their shooting-not Midorima, and I believe with hard training Aomines agility could be possible as well)  I would say that Midorimas, kurokos and kises talents are the most of unrealistic but still.  To this Anime I can say as far as I watched the amv, it looks really good, their might be great techniques if you train hard enough that you could use them in rl. I don't think you can compare them much, but from basketball this one might be more realistic and their is a chance to learn as I said good techniques for starters in basketball, like me. From team play I just loved the improvements of seirin in knb, and also I liked the funny moments there. I still think I prefer knb since it's one of my favourite animes but I will give this one a chance.  By the way before anybody says I don't know anything about real basketball, I will say I liked knb in generall and I am a starter in basketball but I wanted to even play it before I watched the Anime. I am learning the tequnics of shooting and so on from a friend, she plays pretty good and I hope I can improve as much as her.
